To Nature’s heart, I would repair,
   Where calm and beauty reign,
And find a solace resting there,
   To wash away all pain.

The flowers bloom, the rivers flow,
   Each sunset paints anew,
In nature’s care, I’ll let it go,
   Embrace the timeless view.

- Alfred Lord Tennyson
